entry.title: Poland's Vote Provides Donald Tusk With Path Back to Power
entry.content: The ruling Law and Justice Party veered right to tap into Ukraine fatigue, but failed to win enough votes to form a government after a bitter campaign.

entry.title: Dozens of Countries Scramble to Identify More Than 150 Citizens Held Hostage in Gaza
entry.content: Qatar and Turkey position themselves as key intermediaries; Hamas militants “ditched their mobile phones and it was impossible to reach any of them.”

entry.title: Egypt Weighs Letting In Foreigners and Palestinians From Gaza
entry.content: Cairo is is coming under intense pressure to allow refugees to cross the border and escape an Israeli bombing campaign and expected ground invasion.
